
[1]licentious

   LICEN'TIOUS, a. [L. licentiosus.]

   1. Using license; indulging freedom to excess; unrestrained by law or
   morality; loose; dissolute; as a licentious man.

   2. Exceeding the limits of law or propriety; wanton; unrestrained; as
   licentious desires. Licentious thoughts precede licentious conduct.
